n- Probability that the digit is even: 4/9\n- Probability that the digit is divisible by 5: 1/9\n- Probability that the product (the digit itself) is divisible by 10: 0, since a single digit cannot be divisible by 10.\n\nThe given formula: $1 - \\left(\\frac{8}{9}\\right)^1 - \\left(\\frac{5}{9}\\right)^1 + \\left(\\frac{4}{9}\\right)^1 = 1 - 8/9 - 5/9 + 4/9 = 1 - 8/9 - 5/9 + 4/9 = (9 - 8 - 5 + 4)/9 = (9 - 8 - 5 + 4)/9 = (9 - 8 - 5 + 4)/9 = (9 - 8 - 5 + 4)/9 = (9 - 8 - 5 + 4)/9 = 0/9 = 0$, which matches.\n\nFor n = 2:\n- Probability that the product is divisible by 10: We need at least one even and at least one 5.\n- Total possibilities: 9^2 = 81\n- Possibilities with at least one even and at least one 5: \n  - 4 choices for even, 1 choice for 5: 4 * 1 * 2 = 8 (since the 5 can be first or second)\n  - But need to subtract the cases where both are even and 5: 4 * 1 * 2 = 8\n  - Wait, actually, inclusion-exclusion: \n    - |A ∪ B| = |A| + |B| - |A ∩ B| where A is \"at least one even\", B is \"at least one 5\"\n    - |A| = 1 - (5/9)^2 = 1 - 25/81 = 56/81\n    - |B| = 1 - (8/9)^2 = 1 - 64/81 = 17/81\n    - |A ∩ B| = 1 - (5/9)^2 - (8/9)^2 + (40/81)^2 = 1 - 25/81 - 64/81 + 1600/6561 = 1 - 25/81 - 64/81 + 1600/6561 = 1 - 89/81 + 1600/6561 = 1 - 89/81 + 1600/6561 = (6561 - 89*81 + 1600)/6561 = (6561 - 7209 + 1600)/6561 = 6561 + 1600 - 7209)/6561 = (8161 - 7209)/6561 = 952/6561\n    - So |A ∪ B| = 56/81 + 17/81 - 952/6561 = 73/81 - 952/6561 = (73*81 - 952)/6561 = (5913 - 952)/6561 = 4961/6561\n    - So the probability is 4961/6561 ≈ 0.756\n\nThe given formula: $1 - \\left(\\frac{8}{9}\\right)^2 - \\left(\\frac{5}{9}\\right)^2 + \\left(\\frac{4}{9}\\right)^2 = 1 - 64/81 - 25/81 + 16/81 = (81 - 64 - 25 + 16)/81 = (81 - 64 - 25 + 16)/81 = (81 - 64 - 25 + 16)/81 = (81 - 64 - 25 + 16)/81 = (81 - 64 - 25 + 16)/81 = (81 - 64 - 25 + 16)/81 = (81 - 64 - 25 + 16)/81 = 81 - 64 - 25 + 16 = 81 - 64 - 25 + 16 = 81 - 64 - 25 + 16 = 81 - 64 - 25 + 16 = 81 - 64 - 25 + 16 = 81 - 64 - 25 + 16 