The total number of sequences is $9^n$. The number of good sequences is $9^n - 5^n - 8^n + 4^n$, as derived using inclusion-exclusion. The probability is then $\frac{9^n - 5^n - 8^n + 4^n}{9^n} = 1 - \left(\frac{5}{9}\right)^n - \left(\frac{8}{9}\right)^n + \left(\frac{4}{9}\right)^n$, which is the given formula.

